rComments: Very good professor. Put her best effort to make you understand and accessible outside of the class. She is very strict about time arrival and class noise. She treats graduate students like kids that is not expected.

Professor Dolgaleva is truly one of the best professors I've had throughout my undergrad and graduate career. Her lectures are well organized and she explains complex subjects in a way that students can understand. She was always helpful outside of class and she really cares about her students. If you put effort into the course, you will do well.

She is one of the best Professors I have ever met . Her classes are full of learning. She teaches awesome and explains everything in the best possible way. But you have to give frequent inputs towards learning as she can throw pop up quizzes anytime. Overall you will enjoy learning photonic networks.
A lot of quizzes ... If you are late for 5 second you will lose the quiz and have to wait outside the class ... She will give final grade based on these quizzes ...

rComments: I am sure this prof has a mental problem, she treats master student like kids ... and likes to show off being so caring and respectful, although she is not in reality.... Finally she gives some bonuses to students she knows

She is really sweet professor and very caring. She gives really decent grades and wants you to learn something. The course I have taken was an easy course, but I'm sure whatever course she would teach won't be hectic for anyone. She gives you so many chances to get decent grades and she is really inspirational for people who really want to learn.

An excellent prof when it comes to grading, explaining (one-on-one), and has clear topics to follow with a lot of extra material for references. She wants you to pass but the only problem comes when she's actually explaining a lecture in class as she rushes through the material. Either ways, her online notes are useful and can get you a good mark.
